      "span_text": "While potential complications of epidural analgesia such as epidural haematoma or abscess formation and their associated neurological sequelae can be debilitating, they are fortunately extremely rare. As postoperative coagulopathy can be commonly seen following liver resection, the advantages have to be carefully balanced against the risks of epidural catheter placement and removal. The aim of our study was to analyse the success rates and complications of epidural analgesia in liver resections performed with a standardised bilateral subcostal incision without a midline component."
